5. NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Deploy happens automatically on push to main.
  No build step needed — publish dir is "." (repo root).

  netlify.toml key settings:
    [build]  publish = "."
    [functions]  directory = "netlify/functions"

  Cache headers configured for:
    /sw.js              → no-cache (PWA service worker)
    /manifest.json      → 24hr cache
    /SkyeDocx/sw.js     → no-cache
    /SkyeDocx/manifest  → no-cache

  Force a redeploy without code changes:
    git commit --allow-empty -m "force redeploy" && git push origin main

  Netlify CLI (one-off manual deploy):
    netlify deploy --prod


