7. PARTIALS / INJECTED ELEMENTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  js/partials.js
    → Auto-injects header, footer, and a floating "ADMIN MENU" link on every
      page that loads it.
    → Floating link: <a id="adminMenuFloatLink" class="floating-glow-neon">
    → To SUPPRESS the floating admin link on a specific page, add this before
      the partials.js script tag:
        <div id="adminMenuFloatLink" style="display:none;pointer-events:none;"></div>
    → partials.js checks !getElementById('adminMenuFloatLink') before injecting,
      so the pre-placed element blocks it.

  partials/header.html
    → Shared nav. Edit this to update the header/dropdown across all pages.
    → After editing, test on both mobile and desktop (mobile uses hamburger menu).

  js/admin-menu-triggers.js
    → Handles admin shortcut trigger logic. Not the floating button itself.


